research_report:
To add a "Sort by Ascending" checkbox for sorting permission categories in the Add Permissions section, place a checkbox control above the list of categories that toggles an ascending alphabetical sort of those categories. When checked, the frontend sorts the categories by name; when unchecked it shows the original order. This interaction updates immediately without page reload.

### UI Placement and Behavior
- Checkbox labeled **"Sort by Ascending"** positioned directly above the permission categories list.
- Checking the box triggers sorting of displayed permission categories in ascending alphabetical order by their name.
- Unchecking the box returns to the default (unsorted or original) order.
- List updates dynamically on toggle.

### Sorting Logic
- Implement sorting on the client-side if all categories are loaded in the UI.
- Use a stable sort function comparing category names alphabetically.
- If data set is large or dynamically loaded, consider server-side sorting by requesting sorted data when checkbox is checked.

### Code Example (React-style pseudocode)
```jsx
function AddPermissionsSection({ permissionCategories }) {
  const [sortAscending, setSortAscending] = React.useState(false);

  const sortedCategories = React.useMemo(() => {
    if (sortAscending) {
      return [...permissionCategories].sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
    }
    return permissionCategories;
  }, [permissionCategories, sortAscending]);

  return (
    <div>
      <label>
        <input
          type="checkbox"
          checked={sortAscending}
          onChange={() => setSortAscending(!sortAscending)}
        />
        Sort by Ascending
      </label>

      <ul>
        {sortedCategories.map(category => (
          <li key={category.id}>{category.name}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Backend/Frontend Considerations
- If all categories are fetched at once, no backend changes are required.
- For large or paginated data, backend API should support sorting by category name on request.
- Communicate checkbox state to backend for sorted queries when applicable.

### Risks & Mitigations
- UI clutter: Keep checkbox placement clear and minimal.
- Compatibility: Test to ensure sorting does not disrupt role-permission assignment logic.
- Performance: Client-side sorting suits small to medium category sets; fallback to backend if needed.

### Summary
- Add a checkbox control labeled "Sort by Ascending" above permission categories.
- Toggle triggers immediate alphabetical ascending sort client-side or via backend call if required.
- Ensures improved usability without disrupting current permission management workflows.

